headline.main: PROBLEMS OF SUPPLY ARE SOLVED IN TUNISIA; Americans Run Trucks and Trains to Front Lines

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, Feb. 28 (U.P.) -- Difficult supply problems have hampered the American forces in Tunisia, but today fleets of trucks and American-operated railroads can carry more than enough to supply the forces that have gone to the front in the past two months.
abstract: US soldiers role in solving supply problems, Tunis front, described
